Color:
In life, dorsum bluish-purple in ground color, without marking (
Fig.4C
) but sometimes with discontinuous, pale white markings. Underside of body lighter than dorsum with light white marking (
Fig. 4D
). The ground color of ventral side becoming bluish gray with relatively large markings varying from pale white to white. In preservative, dorsal and ventral ground color tending to fade.
